nstrates that police authority is provisional in several senses: shifting across time and space, subject to the availability and movement of resources, and dependent upon shared moral codes and relentless instrumental demands. In the end, she shows that police authority in India is not simply a vulgar manifestation of raw power or the violence of law but, rather, a contingent and volatile social resource relied upon in different ways to help realize human needs and desires in a pluralistic, postcolonial democracy. Provocative and compelling, Provisional Authority provides a rare and disquieting look inside the world of police in India, and shines critical light on an institution fraught with moral, legal and political contradictions.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aJustice, Administration ofxSocial aspectsxIndiaxUttar Pradesh. 0aJustice, Administration ofxSocial aspectszIndiazUttar Pradesh. 0aPolice corruptionxIndiaxUttar Pradesh. 0aPolice corruptionzIndiazUttar Pradesh. 0aPolicexIndiaxUttar Pradesh. 0aPolicezIndiazUttar Pradesh. 4aIndia. 4aauthority. 4acorruption. 4acriminalization. 4ademocracy. 4apolicing. 4aprovisionality. 4asecurity. 4aviolence. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package 2014-2016z978311070422808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package 2016z978311068860308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226403847423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226403847.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-068860-3  UChP eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070422-8  UChP eBook-Package 2014-